text: Duplicaria duplicata, common name the duplicate auger, is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae, the auger snails. ==Description== The size of the shell varies between 20 mm and 93 mm. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs in the Red Sea, in the Indian Ocean off Madagascar and Tanzania; off Japan and the Solomon Islands. ==References== ===Bibliography=== * Terryn, Y. (2007). Terebridae: A Collectors Guide. Conchbooks & Natural Art. 59pp + plates. ==External links== * Category:Terebridae Category:Gastropods described in 1758 Category:Taxa named by Carl Linnaeus
title: Duplicaria duplicata
